txt.en: You have turned in a stack of trophies for a modest reward suitable for a collector such as yourself.

Wanted: Jagged beaks from the gore-crows watching the roads to the east. The vile crebain are enemies of the Eglain, and if you deliver the beaks to me, Gadaric Munce, at The Forsaken Inn, you will earn our favour.
'So often these foes have torn the flesh from our people. This effort will not go unrewarded.\n\n'Thank you.'
'The large crebain, gore-crows, travel the land to the east and are unafraid of our warriors. Often, they will attack. We will favour you more if you assist us and prove your efforts.'
Gadaric Munce of the Eglain offers favour with his people if one can collect jagged beaks from the local crebain.
Deliver the jagged beaks to Gadaric Munce at the Forsaken Inn

You accepted a task to acquire jagged beaks for Gadaric Munce. They can be found on the gore-crows which flock along the road east, beneath the shadow of Weathertop. You can find Gadaric within The Forsaken Inn.
Wanted: Jagged beaks from the gore-crows watching the roads to the east.
